function onLoad()
    params = {

        width          = 0,
        height         = 0,
        font_size      = 270,
        color          = {0, 0, 1},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    
    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
end

table = {
    [""] = "100",
    ["100"] = "200",
    ["200"] = "",
}

function increment()
    local button = self.getButtons()[1]

    self.editButton({index = 0, label=table[button.label]})
end

ObjectStates.LuaScript:
function onLoad()
    params = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        label          = "+100",
        position       = {0, 1, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 0, 0},
        width          = 1000,
        height         = 500,
        font_size      = 300,
        color          = {1, 1, 1},
        font_color     = {0, 0, 0},
        tooltip        = "Left-click to increment your score marker, right-click to increment the city score marker."
    }

    self.createButton(params)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
    local marker

    if alt_click then
        -- ignore right-clicks for now
        -- in the future, right-click will increment the city marker
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('6bff57')
    elseif color == "Green" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('fc3802')
    elseif color == "Yellow" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('e0fb49')
    elseif color == "Red" then
        marker = getObjectFromGUID('0d8495')
    elseif color == "Blue" then
        mark = getObjectFromGUID('eb4ccb')
    else
        return
    end

    marker.call("increment")
end

function onLoad()
    local left = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,

        rotation       = {0, 270, 37},
        label          = "",
        width          = 0,
        height         = 0,
        font_size      = 270,
        color          = {0, 0, 1},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    local right = {
        click_function = "click_func",
        function_owner = self,
        position       = {-0.38, 0.94, 0},
        rotation       = {0, 90, -37},
        label          = "",
        width          = 0,
        height         = 0,
        font_size      = 270,
        color          = {0, 0, 1},
        font_color     = {1, 1, 1},
    }
    
    self.createButton(left)
    self.createButton(right)
end

function click_func(obj, color, alt_click)
end

table = {
    [""] = "100",
    ["100"] = "200",
    ["200"] = "300",
    ["300"] = "",
}

function increment()
    -- Assume that both sides have the same value
    local button = self.getButtons()[1]
    local label = table[button.label]

    self.editButton({index = 0, label=label})
    self.editButton({index = 1, label=label})
end
